explanation: sysconf prototype: needed to confirm whether the called API uses or returns any pointer types (if sysconf took or returned pointers the MISRA const-pointer rule could apply). _SC_CRAY_NCPU and _SC_NPROCESSORS_CONF: the integer constants passed to sysconf—needed to verify they are not macros that expand to pointer expressions. HAVE_SYSCONF, HAS_DECL__SC_CRAY_NCPU, HAS_DECL__SC_NPROCESSORS_CONF: the compile-time macros control which code path is compiled; required to determine if any branch introducing pointer usage is enabled. (Together these symbols let an analyzer determine whether the function actually invokes any pointer-accepting/returning routine or uses pointer expressions that could trigger the MISRA const-pointer rule.)
